		<td><b>RAM cart?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As part of my ongoing experiments I'd like to build a SLROM (MMC1 based) ram cart.  I know I can only access 256KB of data using the ususally MMC1 hardware, but I thought it would be nice to put down a 1MB or even 2MB rams in place of the PRG and CHR ROMS.  To my surprise, I was not able to find SRAM's in those sizes.  Just wanted to check if anyone else has seen them, or if I'm just going crazy.  I'd hate to have to wire in 4 512KB SRAM's, which were the largest I could find.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


